tinyobj gives us the option to parse an obj file _without_ specifying a material
reader. However, even if no material reader has been provided, usages of
"usemtl" will bark at the lack of material. In the case where we're clearly not
reading materials, we shouldn't bother processing the usemtl directives either.

We made an effort to upstream a previous version:
tinyobjloader/tinyobjloader#383
For various reasons, it didn't take. If we are willing to try again, we can
promote this to upstream again and resubmit.

--- tiny_obj_loader.h
+++ tiny_obj_loader.h
@@ -8535,6 +8535,10 @@ static bool LoadObjInternal(attrib_t *attrib, std::vector<shape_t> *shapes,

     // use mtl
     if (sr.match("usemtl", 6) && (sr.peek_at(6) == ' ' || sr.peek_at(6) == '\t')) {
+      if (readMatFn == nullptr) {
+        sr.skip_line();
+        continue;
+      }
       sr.advance(6);
       std::string namebuf = sr_parseString(sr);

@@ -9039,6 +9043,10 @@ static bool LoadObjWithCallbackInternal(StreamReader &sr,

     // use mtl
     if (sr.match("usemtl", 6) && (sr.peek_at(6) == ' ' || sr.peek_at(6) == '\t')) {
+      if (readMatFn == nullptr) {
+        sr.skip_line();
+        continue;
+      }
       sr.advance(6);
       std::string namebuf = sr_parseString(sr);
